Plush Toy: This hillside... it used to be forest. Now it's bare.
Plush Toy: The city wants to reforest it, but the budget is limited. We can't plant everywhere.
Plush Toy: Here's the hard truth: Planting trees is easy. Keeping them alive? That's where most projects fail.
=> decision_1

~ decision_1
Plush Toy: Choose which saplings to plant. Each has trade-offs.
- Native species (slow but sustainable)
	Plush Toy: Native species support local wildlife and survive better long-term. But... it'll take years to see results. Patience is part of sustainability.
	=> set_native
- Exotic fast-growing (quick green cover)
	Plush Toy: Look how green it gets! But... some of these species might outcompete native plants. Fast isn't always better.
	=> set_exotic
- Fruit trees (community benefit)
	Plush Toy: The community loves this! Free food = they'll protect the trees. But the budget... we can plant fewer.
	=> set_fruit

